explanation:
- OS_stream_internal_record_t: needed to know the exact layout and size of stream->stream_name and the type/size of stream->socket_domain so strncpy/strcmp usage and buffer bounds can be checked.
- OS_stream_table: needed to understand the storage backing OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET (table size/extent) to ensure the pointer returned by the macro indexes a valid object and that writing stream_name cannot escape the table.
- OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET: macro/function that maps an object index/token to a pointer; its semantics determine whether the obtained stream pointer is valid and within bounds of the stream structure.
- OS_object_iter_t: definition (including the type and range of iter.token) is required to verify iterator behavior and that iter.token yields valid indices for OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET.
- OS_ObjectIdIterateActive: prototype/semantics used to initialize the iterator; needed to reason about which tokens will be produced and whether any out-of-range tokens could be seen.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorGetNext: behavior/return semantics determine loop termination and whether iter.token is valid before dereferencing the stream pointer.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorDestroy: its behavior may affect iterator state/transaction handling; needed to fully model iterator lifetime and guarantee no use-after-destroy issues.
- OS_ObjectIndexFromToken: used (directly or indirectly via OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET) to convert tokens to array indices; required to check index bounds into the stream table.
- OS_MAX_LOCAL_PATH_LEN: size of old_path/new_path buffers; needed to ensure OS_TranslatePath calls cannot overflow these local buffers.
- OS_TranslatePath: prototype and contract (how many bytes it writes, null-termination guarantees, error codes) are required to verify safe use of old_path/new_path.
- OS_FileRename_Impl: its return codes control whether the iterator/rename of stream_name runs; its semantics are needed for control-flow reasoning about when string operations execute.
- OS_SUCCESS: the success return-code constant used in flow checks; required to understand which branches execute and therefore which string ops occur.
- OS_SocketDomain_INVALID: constant value used in the conditional that gates modification of stream_name; needed to determine when strncpy will be invoked.
- strcmp: standard semantics (read-only access to stream->stream_name and old) are required to ensure the strcmp invocation does not read beyond either string's buffer.
- strncpy: standard semantics (number of bytes copied, null-termination behaviour when source length >= n) are needed to determine whether the way strncpy is used plus the explicit termination assignment prevents writes or accesses beyond stream_name bounds.

Provide these symbols (types, macros, constants, and function contracts) so the analyzer can determine exact buffer sizes, pointer validity, and whether strncpy/strcmp invocations can access or write beyond object bounds.
